After a year+ on the lookout for this elusive Chicago delicacy, I recently had the good fortune of locating & eating a Jim Shoe (aka Gym Shoe). For those not in the know, the Jim Show is a corn beef, roast beef and gyro meat filled sandwich originating from Chicago's South and West sides. I paid $14.99 + tax for a beast of a sandwich from Super Submarine on Ashland. The meat was minced, mixed, and served on soft sub bread, then topped with mayo/tzatziki, yellow mustard, giardiniera, shredded lettuce and tomatoes. A blend of three famous sandwiches creating something amazingly delicious and completely American. From the first bite, I realized things had changed for me. Why have one of the three when you can have ALL THREE. For me, the Jim Shoe has claimed the number one spot as Chicago's best sandwich.  As for the establishment, everyone was friendly and it was exactly what I expected.  Nothing fancy but a perfectly good place to grab the best sandwich around.

Got some delivery from one of my go to restaurants back in the day. Ordered my usual Double Gyro Cheeseburger, Philly Steak and a Gyro Pie.  Deliver was 5 bucks for about 2 miles which was a pain, lucky I had a $5 off coupon for Grubhub which took care of that. First thing I noticed when I got my order was they got one of my soda's wrong. Then, once I got into eating they gave me a spinach puff instead of a gyro pie. If they didn't have any gyro pies they could have called and asked me if they could switch it out or refund me, but they didn't.  Spinach puff was the same as every restaurant in the hood. Gyro burger was prepared really messy. The toppings were just lazily thrown onto the burger and were falling off. Philly steak looked ok and tasted good. Overall everything was good other than a few mishaps. Next time I order anything I'll call in to make sure they got everything correct before they send it out.
